25/04/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The European Commission (EC) will launch an excessive deficit procedure against Bulgaria, Amadeu Altafaj, spokesman for the EC's economic and financial affairs directorate-general, confirmed on Thursday (April 22nd). He added that the process is triggered automatically and follows notification by Eurostat that Bulgaria missed the stability and growth pact benchmark deficit of 3% of GDP. Its deficit was 3.9% of GDP for the first time since joining the EU in 2007. (Dnevnik, bTV, Sofia Echo, Mediapool - 22/04/10)
